article.headline: Smith's double-double paces DePaul's rout of city rival
article.linkText: DePaul in cruise control over Chicago rival Loyola
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Khara Smith scored 17 points and Caprice Smith added 12 to lead No. 14 DePaul to an easy 96-48 victory over winless Loyola of Chicago on Tuesday night.

The Blue Demons (11-1) are off to their best start ever. They were 10-1 in 1985-86 and 2003-04.

Khara Smith grabbed 10 rebounds for the Blue Demons and Erin Carney led the team with five assists. Allie Quigley added 11 points for DePaul, which was 35-for-71 from the floor and led 48-27 at the half.

Danielle Lonie led the Ramblers (0-10) with 10 points, and Marquise Hanser added nine. Loyola made only 16 of 52 shots.
